Overview of Avalanche DEX Liquidity Provider Segmentation and Retention Analysis (Historical Trends from May 2024 to April 2025)
The entire Liquidity Provision analysis on this dashboard captures liquidity addition events (Liquidity Providers' deposit/TVL additions to DEXs on Avalanche) and does not include liquidity removals, pool rewards/harvesting, swap transactions, or LP token minting events. This analysis aims to provide a comprehensive understanding of liquidity provider behavior across Avalanche's DEX ecosystem through the lens of user acquisition, engagement, retention, and monetization. It segments users into distinct tiers based on their liquidity provision volume, tracking their journey from entry to sustained participation while measuring cross-platform engagement patterns and value creation metrics. This analysis serves as a strategic tool for understanding LP behavior patterns, market dynamics, and platform performance within the Avalanche DEX ecosystem, providing actionable insights through the IDG framework.

Liquidity Providers' Journeys and Behaviors

The tiers are based on the total USD volume of liquidity provided by each address:

  1. Whales: Top 1% of providers

  2. Sharks: Next 4% (top 1-5%)

  3. Dolphins: Next 5% (top 5-10%)

  4. Fish: Next 10% (top 10-20%)

  5. Octopus: Next 20% (top 20-40%)

  6. Crab: Next 20% (top 40-60%)

  7. Shrimp: Everyone else (bottom 40%)

of course, the low-tier liquidity providers are always more active but contribute little to the TVL of these DEXs

At a glance, the behavior of Liquidity Providers on Avalanche DEXs shows similar trend patterns to that of DEX traders/users.

The high-value group, although fewer in number and having higher retention rates and LP volumes (in USD), also leads in active months and liquidity provision actions compared to mid-value and low-value liquidity providers.

High-value LPs drive significant value with their consistent activity, but mid and low-value LPs lag in engagement. To boost their participation, Avalanche can introduce tiered LP rewards starting June 2025, incentivizing more liquidity actions across all groups.

The low-tier liquidity providers are always active and looking for the next big thing, but for short term gains. That's why we always have new LPs every month.

Monthly Retained Liquidity Providers (LP Retention)
Whales/Sharks/Dolphins (large LPs) tend to provide stable liquidity, hold positions longer, and are less reactive to changing rewards. Shrimp/Crab (small LPs) often add/remove liquidity quickly and respond more to changes in yields (APYs), making them less stable.

Summary and Actionable Insights

Tier Segmentation

üê≥ Whales (Top 1%): Highest volume providers, crucial for deep liquidity
ü¶à Sharks (1-5%): Significant liquidity providers
üê¨ Dolphins (5-10%): Medium-large liquidity providers
üêü Fish (10-20%): Moderate liquidity providers
üêô Octopus (20-40%): Regular active providers
ü¶Ä Crab (40-60%): Small but consistent providers
ü¶ê Shrimp (Bottom 40%): Retail LPs

Significance for Avalanche Growth

Market Impact

  • Helps identify which LP segments drive most liquidity

  • Reveals retention patterns across different tiers

  • Shows platform preferences among different LP segments

  • Identifies potential areas for liquidity optimization

Key Growth Metrics

Volume Metrics

  • Total LP Actions

  • Volume (USD)

  • Average Volume per LP

  • Average Pools per LP

Retention Metrics

  • Retention Rate %

  • Cohort Retention %

  • Reactivation Rate %

  • Net LP Growth

User Behavior Metrics

Platform Usage

  • Average Platforms per LP

  • Platform-specific pool participation (TraderJoe, Pangolin, Pharaoh, etc.)

  • Average Unique Tokens per LP

  • Swap behavior in LP pools

Business Significance

Operational Insights

  • Helps optimize liquidity mining programs

  • Guides incentive structure design

  • Identifies platform strengths/weaknesses

  • Enables targeted marketing strategies

Risk Management

  • Monitors concentration risk

  • Tracks ecosystem health

  • Identifies potential liquidity gaps

Key Takeaways

Ecosystem Health

  • Multiple active DEXs indicate healthy competition

  • Diverse LP participation across tiers

  • Cross-platform liquidity provision

Areas for Improvement

  • Retention rates across tiers

  • Platform-specific adoption

  • Reactivation strategies for dormant LPs

Growth Suggestions

Short-term Growth (June)

Targeted Incentive Programs

  • Tier-specific liquidity mining rewards

  • Special rewards for multi-pool LPs

  • Cross-platform incentives

User Experience Improvements

  • Simplified LP interface for smaller providers

  • Advanced analytics for whale/shark tiers

  • Better portfolio management tools

Community Engagement

  • Educational content for new LPs

  • Tier-specific community programs

  • Regular AMA sessions with platform teams

Long-term Strategic Initiatives

Platform Development

  • Improved yield optimization tools

  • Better risk management features

  • Enhanced LP analytics dashboards

Ecosystem Growth

  • Cross-chain liquidity bridges

  • New pool types introduction

  • Innovation in LP token utilities

Market Development

  • Institutional LP outreach

  • Strategic partnerships

  • Geographic expansion focus

Action Items for Growth

Immediate Actions

  • Launch tier-specific incentive programs

  • Implement retention improvement strategies

  • Enhance user education initiatives

Medium-term Goals

  • Develop advanced LP tools

  • Improve cross-platform integration

  • Launch institutional LP program

Long-term Objectives

  • Build sustainable LP ecosystem

  • Reduce dependency on incentives

  • Establish market-leading position

This analysis provides a comprehensive framework for understanding and improving Avalanche's DEX ecosystem, with specific focus on liquidity provision and growth strategies. The key is to maintain a balance between attracting new LPs while retaining existing ones, all while ensuring sustainable ecosystem growth.
